==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Syncope
<hw>Syn"co*pe</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>syncope</ets>, <ets>syncopa</ets>, Gr. <?/ a cutting up, a syncope;
akin to <?/ to beat together, to cut up, cut short, weavy;
<grk>sy`n</grk> with + <?/ to strike, cut.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Gram.)</fld> <def>An elision or retrenchment of one or more
letters or syllables from the middle of a word; as, <xex>ne'er</xex> for
<xex>never</xex>, <xex>ev'ry</xex> for <xex>every</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Mus.)</fld> <def>Same as
<er>Syncopation</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A fainting, or swooning. See
<er>Fainting</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>A pause or cessation; suspension.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Revely, and dance, and show,⟦br⟧
Suffer a <qex>syncope</qex> and solemn pause.</q>
<rj><qau>Cowper.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Syncopist</ent>⟦br⟧
